This paper is primarily focused on improving the efficiency of solving large-scale Lasso problems, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is focused on the development and analysis of algorithms that can learn from and make predictions on data. 

The paper also discusses the use of convex optimization techniques and polytope projections, which are common in the fields of numerical analysis and optimization. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) are also likely sub-categories. 

The paper also discusses the use of group Lasso, which is a variant of Lasso that is used for feature selection in group-structured data. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a possible sub-category, as it is focused on the analysis of network-structured data. 

Finally, the paper discusses the use of screening rules, which are a type of feature selection technique that can be used to reduce the computational complexity of optimization problems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a possible sub-category, as it is focused on the analysis and optimization of information processing systems.
